					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It's pretty easy to play around with vspcplay and find out the interfaced used by a bunch of games...<br /><br />Super Metroid maps writes to $2140 to various music effects/cues, and writes to the other three registers to various sound effects.<br />Super Mario World selects track with writes to $2142, and the other three registers select sound effects (each on its own channel).<br /><br />Other games (e.g. FF6) dynamically load patches, so the interface isn't as trivially discoverable.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

